  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - SHADOWKNIGHT</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>HOW TO BEAT TANK CLASSES</font> - <small>Drakulis Darkfury, Brell Serilis</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>I enjoy the fine art of dueling and nothing is better than
going up against someone who has 4 or more lvls on you and
winning or putting up a good fight. This guide is strictly for
dueling tank classes; another sk, war, pally, rog, ranger, or
monk. <br>
****** For lvl 30 to 38 SKs ******<br>
<br>
Key Spells - <br>
<br>
Heat Blood- rarely ever resisted no matter what lvl the target
is. Does a decent amount of damage<br>
<br>
Life Draw- good for refilling your health bar and lower opponents<br>
<br>
Shadow Step- cheap mana cost, lets you put some distance between
you and your opponent, gives you room to cast a spell without
interupttion...and great for annoying anyone =)<br>
<br>
Gather Shadows- to meddiate in peace or to step back and rethink
strategy<br>
<br>
Darkness- good for some damage and slowing down your opponent.
Any tank that was good gear or is a few lvls higher may resist
this half the time.<br>
<br>
Fear- good for fear kiting but I don't recommend it since fear
will be resisted a majority of the time to anyone with good gear
or of a higher lvl.<br>
<br>
Siphon Strength- always useful for some str, uses little mana<br>
<br>
Pet- nice to have, but not needed<br>
<br>
Deadeye- to see invis and better in dark<br>
<br>
<br>
***The Method*** SK vs tank_01<br>
<br>
1. Send pet in<br>
<br>
2. Heat Blood, darkness, fear...shadowstep when the tank_01 gets
to you, finish the series with as many shadowsteps as needed (if
fear or darkness are resisted I don't reccomend trying to recast
it more than once if at all).<br>
<br>
3. move in and melee, hopefully fear stuck so you and your pet
can attack him from behind, if not...be creative and move around
while attacking, (ex. if you are fighting a short race, jump over
him and attack from behind), if fear did stick, shadowstep and
recast when it wears off, if not, try again if you want or save
the mana.<br>
<br>
4. When you get low on health or need to reapply DoTs, back up
and shadowstep. Cast lifedraw/DoTs and shadowstep again and
repeat as needed...this keeps tank_01 off you while your pet is
still on him. If tank_01 attacks your pet melee until he switches
back to you then shadowstep.<br>
<br>
5. By now you should be pretty low on mana, you can either A)
Harm Touch and try to finish tank_01 off<br>
B) gather shadows and medditate some and bandage yourself (note*
this won't work against another SK who can see invis with
deadeye), also realize a warrior will bandage a monk will mend
and pally/ranger will heal themselves. How long this last is up
to you. * Ranger can track but will need some item or help to see
invis. Your pet will be dead by now. <br>
<br>
6. go back and repeat step 4 and 5<br>
<br>
<br>
***** The fight is yours *****<br>
<br>
***Some variations***<br>
you can <br>
1) shadowstep away and let the DoTs and pet beat up on tank_01
until you feel it is safe to melee<br>
<br>
2) fear kite if it isn't resisted (ie- Darkness, fear, heat blood
and melee, reapply as needed)<br>
<br>
some notes-<br>
<br>
if tank_01 is a paladin and likes to blind/root you, he's just
wasting his mana. You can easliy shadowstep away from him while
rooted and cast spells or stay put and melee if you want. If he
blinds you, as long as you have your hotkeys memorized you are
fine. Shadowstep and cast spells until unblinded (you have to
listen for the spell to know if it went off at all) You could
even shadowstep and medditate until he finds you or blind wears
off.<br>
<br>
tank_01 **WILL** out damage you in melee if it is a warrior or
monk so shadowstep is very useful to keep a distance and annoys
them because they can't touch you. <br>
<br>
if tank_01 is a rog or ranger, make sure you have deadeye on you
for the fight since they might camo/sneak<br>
<br>
**********************************************<br>
<br>
Most importantly have fun. Make a bunch of emotes and duel taunt
hotkeys for before and during (if you dare) the fight to poke fun
at your opponent.<br>
Use %t for tank_01's name to appear<br>
<br>
some favorites are... <br>
<br>
/say You have ruined your homelands tank_01, you'll not ruin
mine!<br>
<br>
/laugh say laughs hysterically when tank_01 challenges him. <br>
<br>
/point say points to the chachi he is going to kill<br>
<br>
<br>
*** Go out and spread evil ***<br>
</p>
</td></tr>
